md:
giải nghĩa từ "dummy" sang tiếng việt; đưa ra nghĩa tiếng việt theo từ loại và đưa ra câu ví dụ, các từ liên quan.

Dummy (noun) - Bù nhìn, người giả

* Meaning: A person or thing that is used to deceive or trick others.
* Example sentence: The police used a dummy in a sting operation to catch the thief.
* Related words: fake, pretend, decoy, mock

Dummy (verb) - Làm giả, giả vờ

* Meaning: To pretend or make something appear to be something else.
* Example sentence: The magician dummied the audience into thinking the trick was real.
* Related words: fake, pretend, deceive, trick

Dummy (adjective) - Giả, không có thực

* Meaning: Not real or genuine; fake or artificial.
* Example sentence: The dummy ID card was easily detected by the security guard.
* Related words: fake, pretend, artificial, bogus

Note: The word "dummy" can have different meanings depending on the context in which it is used. The above definitions and examples are just a few of the possible ways the word can be used.
